						<summary>

						<p>Slab setup in a field out side the village.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Haihaya Kumāra Allahulidēva 13th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It records a grant of land sowable with one <hi rend="italic">khanduga</hi> seed by <hi rend="italic">mahāmaṇḍalēśvara</hi> Kumāra Allahulidēva of the Haihaya family to the temple of Lakshminārāyaṇadēva built by Śarvadēva-seṭṭi of Baḷagaranūru.</p>						

						<p>It is in characters of the 13th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>[Note: The above note is based on the Annual Report, since both the estampage and the transcript are found missing for verification].</p>						

